{
  "stem": "1061.5",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "Picture was taken in 1946, while I attended that school.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "As you could see, the top row, the tallest kids, that's us, the so-called high school group.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "The rest are the other kids who lived at the DP camp at the same time as I did.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "And there is an arrow here that points directly to where I am located in this picture, wearing a white blouse, open white blouse, over a jacket.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "[POINTS] This DP camp was very much oriented toward the-- reestablishing a childhood in a lot of us who have suffered through the war.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "And I have absolutely the fondest memories of that school.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 44,
      "text": "And from here, we left for America.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 45,
      "text": "And I spent here not quite a year.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 46,
      "text": "As a matter of fact, about two or three years ago, our high school group had a reunion in Pennsylvania.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 47,
      "text": "And we met all of us.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 48,
      "text": "Of course, this is 50 years later-- no, not 50 years-- 48 years later.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 49,
      "text": "And it was really wonderful having met all these people who came from everywhere.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 50,
      "text": "And, and we were reminiscing.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 51,
      "text": "And interestingly enough, everybody had just about the fondest memories of, of, of the relationships between the kids and the teachers and, and between-- and the whole setup, that was to compensate for our misery during the war, was just absolutely indescribable.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 52,
      "text": "Well, this is my diploma from Indiana University, where I graduated in February, 1953.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 53,
      "text": "And of course, Victor came.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 54,
      "text": "My husband, Victor, came to my graduation.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 55,
      "text": "And it was just absolutely wonderful.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 56,
      "text": "And again, I have the most wonderful memories of my time in Indiana, of my educational experience, of my living in the Midwest-- away from all that preceded my coming there-- and also being away from New York, which is very much European, having found myself for the first time in a real American setting and loving it.",
      "word_count": 58
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 57,
      "text": "Even though Bloomington was a college community exclusively, I still found myself, as I used to call it, inhaling America, inhaling through America at Bloomington.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 58,
      "text": "And this is my graduation diploma, of which I'm very proud.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 59,
      "text": "Well, this is a family of my-- a picture of my own family, during one of our greater family reunions, of which we always have many.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 60,
      "text": "We have-- we have reunions at the drop of a hat.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 61,
      "text": "Well, this is one of these reunions where all the sisters and the husbands and the children come together, and we have great fun.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 62,
      "text": "Well, anyhow, this was taken in 1991.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 63,
      "text": "At the top is Victor, my husband.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 64,
      "text": "Next to him, I am.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 65,
      "text": "On the-- below us, going from the left to the right, is our other older son, Harry, who is a lawyer, lives in Manhattan.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 66,
      "text": "His wife Cheryl, who lives in Manhattan with him.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 67,
      "text": "And their little son, Max, who is now six years old.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 68,
      "text": "And the gentleman-- the young fellow who is holding Max is our younger son, Paul, who is a geologist and lives in Albuquerque, New Mexico.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 69,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] And we are, again, as close a family as they come.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 70,
      "text": "And that means extended close family, and I mean this with all the other members of-- all the cousins.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 71,
      "text": "And I think we're making up for all that happened before.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
